Setup the conda environment using the environment.yml file provided in the root directory.

fileExp.py lauches the demo. Execute it using "python fileExp.py"

Once the demo GUI is launched:
There will be two buttons on the top right corner, named, 1) Browse folders to select input folder   2) Use Webcam Input. Click on one of them.

If "Use Webcam Input" is chosen, input will be taken from webcam.
If "Browse folders to select input folder" is chosen, one file browsing dialog will open up, one can browse through folders in the system to choose the folder containing input images.

Finally, select what results you want to display on the screen by selecting the checkboxes accordingly and click on "Start Demo" button.


NOTE: 
For any installation issue refer to the original repositories.
Depth estimation - https://github.com/JunjH/Revisiting_Single_Depth_Estimation 
Semantic segmentation - https://github.com/CSAILVision/semantic-segmentation-pytorch
Object detection - https://github.com/andy-yun/pytorch-0.4-yolov3
